指湿土，尤指雨后稀泥、污泥。

bilingual.target: 泥土变成了棕色和黑色。

bilingual.source: They pull Robin out of the mud.
bilingual.target: 他们把罗宾从泥里拉出来。

bilingual.source: It turned out there was mud all over the kitchen.
bilingual.target: 原来厨房里到处都是泥。

bilingual.source: He ground and mixed the plants, berries, rocks and mud.
bilingual.target: 他磨碎并混合了植物、浆果、岩石和泥土。

bilingual.source: He tipped the plants, berries, rocks and mud onto the floor.
bilingual.target: 他把植物、浆果、石头和泥倒在地板上。

bilingual.source: During the afternoon we went to see the hippos in the mud, then the pandas.
bilingual.target: 下午我们去看了泥里的河马，然后是熊猫。

bilingual.source: My car got stuck in the mud.

bilingual.target: 泥土附着在他的鞋子上。

list.abstract: MUD (/ˈmʌd/; 原指 Multi-User Dungeon 多使用者迷宫[1]，后又被称为 Multi-User Dimension 多使用者空间与 Multi-User Domain 多使用者领土)，台湾使用者通常直接称呼为MUD。通常将缩写字直译为“网络泥巴”或是简称“泥巴”(英文 mud 的意思为泥巴)。是一款多人即时的虚拟世界，通常以文字描述为基础。 MUD 结合了角色扮演、砍杀、玩家与玩家对战、互动小说与在线聊天等元素，玩家可以阅读或查看房间、物品、其他玩家、非玩家角色的描述，并在虚拟世界中做特定动作。 玩家通常会通过输入类似自然语言的指令来与虚拟世界中的其他玩家互动。

yingyinNormal.en: Sorry, George. It's only mud.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对不起，乔治。只是些泥而已。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, dear.Mummy! We splashed daddy’s football shirt with mud.
yingyinNormal.zh: 噢，天哪。妈妈！我们把泥弄到爸爸的足球衫上了。

yingyinNormal.en: Daddy Pig has rescued the kite! Oh, dear. Everyone is covered in mud. It's only mud.
yingyinNormal.zh: 猪爸爸够到了树枝上的风筝！糟糕，大家身上都是泥。 大家都脏了。

yingyinNormal.en: It looks like a square of tin mud. Mortar is a very special kind of mud that sticks bricks together.
yingyinNormal.zh: 看上去像一团“噗噗”响的稀泥。砂浆这其实是一种非常特殊的泥，他能把砖块都粘在一块。

yingyinNormal.en: It looks like a square of tin mud. Mortar is a very special kind of mud that sticks bricks together.
yingyinNormal.zh: 看上去像一团“噗噗”响的稀泥。砂浆这其实是一种非常特殊的泥，他能把砖块都粘在一块。

yingyinNormal.en: Edith! What did you put on my desk? A mud pie.
yingyinNormal.zh: 伊迪丝！你把什么放我桌上了？泥巴派

yingyinNormal.en: It's only a patch of mud. Come on, Gertrude. You can make it. Come on, bus. You can make it. The bus is stuck in the mud. Oh bother.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这只是一滩泥而已。来吧，格特鲁德，你可以过去的！来吧，巴士，你也可以的！巴士陷进了泥里去了。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, Daddy pig, look at the mess you're in. It's only mud.
yingyinNormal.zh: 噢看呐，猪爸爸，瞧瞧你身上多脏啊。

yingyinNormal.en: We splashed Daddy's football shirt with mud. Oh. Don't worry. We'll just wash it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 爸爸的足球服被我们弄脏了，上面都是泥。别担心！我们洗一下就好。

yingyinNormal.en: What a lot of mud. We don't want to get stuck. Maybe we should go a different way.
yingyinNormal.zh: 突然路上出现了一滩泥！这会让我们都陷进泥里的，或许我们换一条路吧。

yingyinNormal.en: I've got an idea. Grandpa Pig's train can tow me out of the mud. Good thinking, Miss Rabbit.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我想到有什么办法啦！猪爷爷的火车可以帮我拿出来！是个好主意兔小姐。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, dear. Mummy. We splashed daddy's football shirt with mud. Oh. Don't worry. We'll just wash it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 噢，糟糕。妈妈！爸爸的足球服被我们弄脏了，上面都是泥。别担心！我们洗一下就好。

yingyinNormal.en: Sheldon. Hold on. Trying to figure out how to get the bucket so I can carry the mud past the dragon.
yingyinNormal.zh: 谢尔顿。等一下，我正在思考如何能拿到桶，这样我就能扛着泥土越过那条龙了。

yingyinNormal.en: I wouldn't have washed it, but I came off, and it was full of mud. You'll just have to do your best.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我本来不想洗的，但我落马了，头发上全是泥，你得尽全力了。

yingyinNormal.en: George, you're making the car all muddy again. I will wash the mud off. Peppa, don't use the muddy water.
yingyinNormal.zh: 乔治，你看你又把车子给弄脏啦！让我来把泥洗掉吧。

yingyinNormal.en: George, you're making the car all muddy again! I will wash the mud off. Peppa, don't use the muddy water.
yingyinNormal.zh: 乔治，你看你又把车子给弄脏啦！让我来把泥洗掉吧。

yingyinNormal.en: What? We've been through the mud, the shit, the blood. And I've saved your ass more times than I can count.
yingyinNormal.zh: 干嘛？我们一起风风雨雨流血流汗，我都数不清救过你多少次了。

yingyinNormal.en: Hi Pops! Mud and Sweet potatoes. Pops! Who is that? What? Oh, hey Buddy. How you been, old-timer? Paralyzed.
yingyinNormal.zh: 波普！棉花糖和甜土豆。波普！是谁？怎么了？你好啊，小巴。你还好吗，老者？瘫着啊。

yingyinNormal.en: They may look like honeycomb, but these mud brick blocks are used to air-dry millions of grapes into raisins.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这些泥砖块也许看起来像蜂窝，但是它们是用来将数以百万级的葡萄风干成葡萄干的。

yingyinNormal.en: I'll pass you onto the next rescue service. Hello, fire service. I'm stuck in the mud. Can you rescue me, please?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我帮你转给下一个救援的人吧你好，消防队我被困在泥里了，你能来救我吗?

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>

examination_example.sentence: Pyle was famous for covering the human side of the war, writing about the dirt-snow-and-<highlight>mud</highlight> soldiers, not how many miles were gained.
examination_example.sentence_trans: Pyle以报道战争的人性方面而闻名，他写的是在肮脏的雪和泥中作战的士兵，而不是行军了多少英里。
